comment: If there is a cofinal map from ` A ` to ` B ` , then they have the same cofinality. This was used as Definition 11.1 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 100, who defines an equivalence relation cof ` ( A , B ) ` and defines our ` cf ( B ) ` as the minimum ` B ` such that cof ` ( A , B ) ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 20-Mar-2013.)
